@DATABASE
@index index
@node MAIN "The Music Web"
    The Music Web is an environment that lets you do extensive
    manipulation of MIDI event streams in real time.  It is a
    `diagram' based environment, which means that you build the
    configuration you want to perform the desired processing
    directly by placing elements and connecting them together
    on the screen.

        @{" Overview         " LINK Reference.GUIDE/overview}     What and Why
        @{" Requirements     " LINK Reference.GUIDE/prereq}     Hardware and Software
        @{" Quick Start      " LINK Reference.GUIDE/newbie}     Running the Demos
        @{" Reference        " LINK Reference.GUIDE/MAIN}     Using the Web
        @{" MIDI Modules     " LINK Modules.GUIDE/MAIN}     The current set of functions
        @{" Examples         " LINK Examples.GUIDE/MAIN}     Some demo configurations
        @{" Ideas            " LINK Misc.GUIDE/ideas}     Exploring how to use the MusicWeb
        @{" Author           " LINK Reference.GUIDE/distrib 60}     How to contact
        @{" Things to Come   " LINK future}     What's still needed...


  This AmigaGuide documentation is in several parts:
     this `directory' section: `MusicWeb.GUIDE';
     the main reference to using the Web: `Reference.GUIDE';
     descriptions of the MIDI modules: `Modules.GUIDE';
        (the descriptions themselves are actually in `Modules_1.GUIDE',
        `Modules_2.GUIDE, and others, so these must be available.)
     description of the included examples: `Examples.GUIDE'.
     other topics: `Misc.GUIDE'

  You can browse the other guides independently, but the main contents page
  above may be the best road map.  Links placed at strategic points will
  also take you between worlds where it seems appropriate. (I have avoided
  scattering links too liberally, both because of the work involved and
  because I feel it is likely to disrupt reading of the local stuff...)

  A complete overall list of nodes is available in the `Index'.  (I'm
  afraid it's not an alphabetic word index, just a list of the nodes
  by category.)

@endnode

@node future "Things to Come"

 Things to Come
================

    There are obviously many ways in which the MusicWeb can be made
    much more useful and versatile.  (As I've emphasized elsewhere,
    though, how much actually gets done depends intimately on people's
    response to this release...)  In the meantime, development will
    proceed according to my own needs.

    More modules are needed to manipulate `Sequences'.  Things like
    variable playback tempo and some editing facilities (although
    the MusicWeb is not really intended to supplant your Sequencer)
    are obvious requirements.  The Sequence structure has some
    as yet `hidden' extensions that I hope to use in some novel
    ways in the future.

    Seriously missing is a mechanism for SysEx messages.  I'd hoped
    to have this in the current version, but time was getting on, so
    I decided to defer it.

    `Control Messages' are only at the beginning of their utility.
    I would like to eventually be able to convtrol virtually all the
    parameters of individual elements through these messages, and to
    be able to originate them in a wider variety of ways (in response
    to particular chords or sequences for example).

    The set of modules is probably endlessly expandable; exactly which
    ones will come along next I'm not yet certain. I want things like
    rhythm generators and other MIDI event generators, for one thing.
    Many of my ideas depend on the implementation of Control Information,
    so I'll leave them for now.

@endnode

